body: "## Evidence (review pass #90, 2026-07-15)\n\nTwo pm extension packages exist as TWO independent live implementations each, with no canonical pointer:\n\n- **beads**: external npm `pm-beads@2026.7.13` (unscoped, repo unbraind/pm-beads, installs via `pm install github.com/unbraind/pm-beads --global`; capabilities: import + export + `beads-validate`/`beads-diff` commands + `bead_id` schema field) vs in-repo `packages/pm-beads` (`@unbrained/pm-beads@2026.7.15`, private:true, first-party catalog, import-only per README). Divergent feature sets, divergent versions, different package identities.\n- **todos**: external npm `pm-todos@2026.7.11` (unscoped, repo unbraind/pm-todos) vs in-repo `packages/pm-todos` (`@unbrained/pm-todos@2026.7.15`, private:true). Closed items pm-13bn (registerImporter/Exporter migration) and pm-ybfj (beads/todos runtime dedupe) only ever touched the in-repo pair.\n\nAgents/users can install either implementation and get different behavior; fixes land in one and not the other.\n\n## Dependency-range spread across the 18 external pm-* repos (verified 2026-07-15)\n\n- Floors span `^2026.7.5` → `^2026.7.13`; floors are not verified against the API surface actually used (caret on date-based versions floats within the year, so most resolve to latest — the floor is documentation, currently unaudited).\n- `pm-ops` pins exact `2026.7.13` (never floats → guaranteed staleness).\n- external `pm-beads` uses unbounded `>=2026.7.10` (silently crosses the 2027 year-major boundary).\n\n## Fix direction\n\nPick the canonical home per package (extend, never a third implementation), archive/redirect the other, document capability parity + migration. Define one ecosystem range convention (caret year-range with a floor verified by the pm-vnjh reusable smoke harness or the pm-o8um Verified-tier checks) and fix the two outliers.\n\n## Cleared this pass (do not re-investigate)\n\nExternal consumers (pm-graph/pm-web/pm-github/pm-changelog + companion examples) import ONLY official subpaths (`./sdk`, `./sdk/runtime`, `./sdk/testing`) — no deep `dist/` imports anywhere in the org; pm-graph's SDK imports are type-only."
